VBefitting musical tribute
p3
sVnews
p4
VCommemorating the 70th birthday of its former president late L.S.R. Krishna Sastry, Visakha Music Academy organised a vocal recital by the recipient of L.S.R.K. Memorial award in 2007, Duddu Radhika, at Kalabharathi. Radhika, the winner of the gold m\u000aedal for topping the University in M.A. (Music) of AU and the recipient of young talent award and scholarship from the Department of Culture, Govt. of India, astonishingly exploited the melody in her voice to the hilt.Rendering chosen compositions with technical virtuosity, she sang her way into the hearts of all listeners.Her repertoire for the evening comprisedSriraga varnam,Kanjadalayathakshiof Dixitar (Kamalamanohari) with brief but beautifulraagaalapana,Endukunirdayaof Thyagaraja (Harikambhoji) embellished with erudite expression of manodharma inaalapanaandswaram,Sudhamayiof Mutthai Bhagavatar (Amrithavarshini), expansive expatiation ofAnudinamunuof Ramnad Srinivasayyangar (Begada), scholarly execution of a similar exercise renderingYemeechesithenemiof Thyagaraja (Todi), aTarangamin Bilhari and aJavaliin Khamas, M. Neeladri Rao from Vizianagaram on violin and local artiste S. Subrahmanyam on mridangam rendering conformable accompaniment and scholarly manodharma contributed splendour.
